## Axis Styling

It's possible to set a padding between elements in a polar chart's `angle` axis by using two options:

-   `paddingInner` controls the padding between column groups.
-   `groupPaddingInner` controls the padding between columns within a group.

```js
axes: [
    {
        type: 'angle-category',
        groupPaddingInner: 0.25,
        paddingInner: 0.25,
    },
    {
        type: 'radius-number',
    },
];
```

{% chartExampleRunner title="Nightingale Sector Padding" name="nightingale-padding" type="generated" options="{ \"enterprise\": true }" /%}

To create a hole in the middle, use the `innerRadiusRatio` option in the polar `radius` axis:

```js
axes: [
    {
        type: 'angle-category',
    },
    {
        type: 'radius-number',
        innerRadiusRatio: 0.5,
    },
];
```

{% chartExampleRunner title="Nightingale Hole in the Middle" name="nightingale-hole" type="generated" options="{ \"enterprise\": true }" /%}

Please see the API reference for more polar axes style options.

